76561198069278936,Recommended,460960,28453582,"Posted: 18 December, 2016",all,Nikolae,"The Deed Dynasty is a sequel to The Deed. It features three new murder scenarios set in three different time periods with different casts, they are all (almost) up to par with the original though there is little variety. The original had a bit more depth, such as flashbacks that could be encountered in the household, but overall all murder scenarios are of a good quality. However, despite them taking place in different time periods they are all quite similar, since while the story and characters change the mechanics do not. It also does not expand on the original formula, it is the same game except three times as large. With that said, I liked the first game, meaning I also like this one. The dialogue trees are quite intricate and do remember a lot of details, and with the numerous ways to assassinate the targets you can get lots of different endings. The writing itself is good, and the characters, while not memorable, certainly do feel real. If you like interactive storytelling I would reccomend this to you, especially with its low price. However, if we ever get a third game I would like to see some innovation in the mechanics or simply even more reactive dialogue trees. Overall, I say buy it."
