,Recommended,460960,28366101,"Posted: 14 December, 2016",all,LuckyRoot,"To summarize it simply, it is a very cost-efficient, well-written and designed murder scheming simulator. The gameplay involves gathering gossips about others, hiding your true motive by choosing conversations carefully, selecting from a variety of weapons, and using certain evidences all in order to frame others (or make it look like a suicide) and ultimately get away with murder. There are a wide number of outcomes based on your every action and interaction with others.The game is in fact a sequel for the game ""The Deed"". To be precise, it is a sequel that is a prequel which expands on the ""Bruce"" bloodline introduced in the first game with 3 new stories set in older eras. While the first game only had one scenario, ""The Deed: Dynasty"" is, in a sense, like an expansion pack which maintains the general gameplay formula and offers 3 new scenarios with a lot more interesting characters, stories, and motives for murder.While I had never been a fan of such genre, this game has definitely enlightened me to it with the abundant amount of various paths and outcomes it offers under the objective of murder. It is certainly an experience worth trying out for its generous price."
