76561198224384696,Recommended,460960,31940589,Posted: 24 May,all,KsiAura,"At first I bought the game on sale, I hadn't played it until a few months later... Only to find a great game with 3 stories. The main characters seem to be related, only in different time periods. Much like Hitman, you have a variety of ways to murder your target. The goal of the game is to not get caught, as you may plant evidence on others etc.While it is a great time killer, I wish there were more stories! Altough the game is only 3$ I think the devs could have made a few extra stories. Non the less, I highly recommend this game. If you are going to buy it however I feel you should get the bundle that includes ""The Deed"" and ""The Deed; Dynasty"""
76561198117493929,Recommended,460960,31851649,Posted: 19 May,all,Mayumi Sato,"I loved the original game so I was buying this one more as a way of paying back to the original, free game but this one is pretty cool as well and have nice story lines and different sceneries, characters and dramas. However, it's a bit odd how the levels become easier instead of harder. I started from the bottom just by random luck and I noticed not only the difficulty increasing but the story becoming a little worse. Third level is the most easy and interesting. Second level is a bit hard but still have a pretty nice story. First level has a nice setting, but is not as intriguing as the other levels and is pretty hard.Anyway, nice to have multiple levels with this kind of puzzle since I really like it. This is a very good game in general and I totally recommend you to check it, especially if you liked the first one."
